\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  officinale}: Middle and upper leaves deeply and broadly decurrent, and the stem distinctly winged. Stem, leaves, pedicels and calyces more or less densely hairy and setose. {\i Throughout the range of the species}.
