\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b uliginosum}(A. Kerner) Nyman,{\i  Consp.} 509 (1881): Leaves, even the uppermost, not or shortly and narrowly decurrent. Stem and leaves only sparsely covered with very short, stiff setae and densely verrucose-hispid. Sepals with stiff, apical setae, otherwise more or less glabrous. •{\i  E.C. Europe}.
