\pard\f0\fs28 {\b  S. floribundum} R. J. Shuttlew. ex Buckn.,{\i  Jour. Linn. Soc. London} ({\i Bot}.){\b  41}: 531 (1913) ({\i S. mediterraneum} F. W. Schultz, non Koch), an asperous-hispid plant with the calyx lobed to ¼-½, dirty white corolla with the lobes not recurved, scales with all the marginal papillae similar, about 1½ times as long as wide, the connective not projecting beyond the thecae and abortive pollen, is probably a hybrid of {\b 1} and some other species; it was known from S. France (Var), but has not been found for 75 years.
