\pard\f0\fs28    3. {\b S.} × {\b uplandicum} Nyman, {\i Syll.} 80 (1854) ({\i S. asperum} × {\i officinale}). Intermediate between the parents. Stem up to 2 m. Leaves never cordate, the upper sessile, shortly decurrent or more or less amplexicaul. Calyx 5-7 mm; lobes usually acute. Corolla 12-18 mm, pink at first, turning blue, or persistently violet. Scales as in {\b 1} but less wide at the base. 2n = 36.{\i  Formerly cultivated for fodder, and naturalized; also of spontaneous local origin.} [Au Be Br Da Fe Ga Hb Ho No Su.]
